The composition role "ruleCatalogue" specifies the portrayal rule catalogue component of a portrayal catalogue.
SY_GraphicsFill specializes SY_AreaFill as an abstract graphic element of an area fill. This type is realized by a fill in a defined graphics language.
SY_GraphicsFill specializes the type "SY_AreaFill" as a graphic representation of an area fill. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.
The operation "pointSymbolCRS" returns the coordinate reference system of the point symbol presentation.
machine readable name for the symbol
reference to the full details of the symbol specification
The composition role "symbolCatalogue" specifies the portrayal feature catalogue component of a portrayal catalogue.
SY_PointSymbol specializes SY_Presentation as abstract type for point symbol presentation.

SY_LineStyle specializes SY_Presentation as an abstract line style. The line style has a coordinate reference system defined at every point along its path, which has an x-axis that is tangential to the path at that point. The line style also has a one dimensional coordinate reference system that is define along the path of the line style.
The operation "lineCRS" returns a one dimensional coordinate reference system that is define along the path of the line pattern.

The operation "localCRS" shall accept a real value as input and return a coordinate reference system. The parameter "measure" specifies the measure along the path of the line pattern specifying the origin of the coordinate reference system. The x-axis is tangential to the path at that point.
SY_GraphicsLinePattern specializes the type "SY_LinePattern" as a graphic representation of the line pattern. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.

SY_PointSymbolLinePattern specializes the type "SY_LinePattern" as a pattern of repeated point symbols along the path of the line pattern. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.
SY_CompoundLinePattern specializes the type "SY_LinePattern" as a compound of multiple subpatterns. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.
SY_AreaFill specializes SY_Presentation as an abstract area fill. The area fill has a coordinate reference system defined for the fill area.
The operation "lineCRS" returns a two dimensional coordinate reference system that is defined for the fill area.
SY_TransformedAreaFill specializes the type "SY_AreaFill" as a geometricaly transformed fill. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.
SY_CompoundAreaFill specializes the type "SY_AreaFill" as a compound of multiple subfills. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.
SY_PatternFill specializes the type "SY_AreaFill" as a pattern fill with a tile pattern of point symbols. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.
SY_HatchFill specializes the type "SY_AreaFill" as a hatch fill. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.
SY_GraphicsStyle specializes SY_LineStyle as an abstract graphic element of a line style. This type is realized by a pen style in a defined graphics language.

SY_Presentation is the abstract root type for presentation. It defines a generic presentation with browse graphics and a portrayal feature type for the interface with parameters, where the parameters to the presentation are the attributes of the portrayal feature type.
The optional attribute "browseGraphic" specifies graphics that may be used as metadata for the presentation and used to give a sample of the appearance of the presentation.
PC_PortrayalCatalogue specializes CT_Catalogue containing a portrayal rule catalogue as well as a portrayal feature catalogue and as such contains the elements necessary for a portrayal.
PC_PortrayalCatalogue specializes the abstract type "CT_Catalogue" for portrayal. As such it shall implement all inherited attributes, operations and associations.
SY_TransformedLineStyle specializes SY_LineStyle as a geometric transformation of the original style. The transformed line style may either be inline or referenced as a portrayal feature.

The attribute "translation" specifies the translation of the pattern relative to the superpattern in two dimensions: along the path of the line pattern, and perpendicular to the path of the line pattern.
The attribute "scale" specifies the scaling of the pattern perpendicular to the path of the line pattern.
The attribute "stretch" specifies the stretch of the pattern along the path of the line pattern.

SY_CompoundAreaFill specializes SY_AreaFill as a composition of subfills. The subfills may either be inline or referenced as portrayal features. The elements of the composition are ordered for display.
The attribute "transformation" uses homogeneous coordinates to define a geometric transformation of a point symbol.

The code list "SY_RelativePlacement" names the possible relative placements of a presentation, in particular point symbols. A placement can either be relative the coordinate reference system of the portrayal or relative to the coordinate reference system of the superordinate presentation within which the presentation is being placed.

SY_CompoundPointSymbol specializes SY_PointSymbol as a composition of subsymbols. The subsymbols may either be inline or referenced as portrayal features. The elements of the composition are ordered for display.

SY_CompoundLineStyle specializes SY_LineStyle as a composition of substyles. The substyles may either be inline or referenced as portrayal features. The elements of the composition are ordered for display.
SY_TransformedAreaFill specializes SY_AreaFill as a geometric transformation of the original fill. The transformed area fill may either be inline or referenced as a portrayal feature.
The attribute "transformation" uses homogeneous coordinates to define a geometric transformation of an area fill.

The attribute "relativePlacement" specifies if the transformation is relative to the superordinate presentation, relative to the portrayal coordinate reference system, or not applicable. The default value of this attribute is "portrayal".

SY_PointSymbolLineStyle is a pattern of repeated point symbols along the path of the line style. The symbol is repeated at regular intervals and may have a masking, which masks out the underlying superstyle around the point symbol. For the point symbol not to be rendered at the unit length intervals but offset a line style transformation may be used.

The attribute "unitLength" specifies the repetition interval length for the point symbol along the path of the line pattern. The interval is given in the coordinate reference system of the line pattern (operation "lineCRS").
The attribute "masking" specifies the extent of the masking border masking out the underlying superpattern around the point symbol.
SY_HatchFill is a hatch fill created by filling an area with repeated application of a line style, applied in a specified direction, spaced evenly over a fill area, space with a specified interval.
The attribute "direction" specifies the direction of the hatch lines.
The attribute "interval" specifies the interval between the hatch lines.
The operation "hatchCRS" returns a one dimensional coordinate reference system that is define along the path of a hatch line.
SY_PatternFill is a fill created by filling an area with repeated application of point symbol tiles. The tiles are applied regularly at intervals defined by two vectors.
The attribute "tileOffset" specifies two vectors that describe the offsets of the tiles in two directions.
The operation "tileCRS" returns the coordinate reference system for a tile of the area fill.
